cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper deals with machine learning tasks and structured outputs, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves image segmentation and matching problems from vision, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper presents a new algorithm for learning discrete exponential family models, which could be of interest to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
